body: <a href="#"><img alt="P1" src="https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p1.svg?v=7" align="top"></a> **`CopilotAuth.token` should use `Secret<String>`**

Per the project security policy (CLAUDE.md): _"Use `secrecy::Secret<String>` for all passwords/keys/tokens. `expose_secret()` only at consumption point."_

The `token` field holds a short-lived Copilot API token. Storing it as a plain `String` means it can appear in heap dumps and debug output in cleartext. The `access_token` field in `OAuthTokens` (read at lines 257–258 just before being converted into a `CopilotAuth`) is already wrapped in `Secret<String>` — stripping the wrapper when moving it into this struct defeats the protection.

```suggestion
struct CopilotAuth {
    token: secrecy::Secret<String>,
    base_url: String,
    /// `true` when the endpoint is an enterprise proxy that only supports
    /// streaming chat completions.
    is_enterprise: bool,
}
```

All callers that build the `Authorization` header (`format!("Bearer {}", auth.token)`) would then become `format!("Bearer {}", auth.token.expose_secret())`.

