body: <a href="#"><img alt="P1" src="https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p1.svg?v=7" align="top"></a> **Enterprise guard fires before Responses-API check in `complete()`**

The `is_enterprise` early-return at line 698 executes before `needs_responses_api()` at line 703. For an enterprise user on `gpt-5.4` or `gpt-5.2-pro` (which must use `/responses`), the code routes to `collect_streamed_completion` — which POSTs to `/chat/completions`. The enterprise proxy will return an error for those models.

By contrast, `stream_with_tools` (lines 793–798) correctly evaluates `needs_responses_api` first, so the streaming path is unaffected. Only `complete()` has the inverted order.

Swap the guards:

```suggestion
        if needs_responses_api(&self.model) {
            return self.complete_responses(messages, tools).await;
        }

        // Enterprise proxy only supports streaming — delegate to the
        // streaming path and collect the result.
        if auth.is_enterprise {
            return collect_streamed_completion(self.client, &auth, &self.model, messages, tools)
                .await;
        }
```

